{{Noticebox/Community}}{{Stub|This list needs to be expanded, and formatted in accordance to the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRCWiki:Manual of Style|Manual of Style]]}}This page is dedicated to the various cultures of VRChat. A [[wikipedia:Culture|culture]] is a dynamic abstraction or concept, of '''common or shared groups''' of interests, activities, or social behaviors and norms among a community or population.

== Overview ==
[[File:Mirrors.webp|thumb|A group of users socializing in front of a [[Mirrors|mirror]].]]
An easier way to understanding VRChat culture, is by interacting with other users through observation, or participating in healthy mutual activities on the platform. Some users create [[groups]] and [[Calendar|calendar events]] to find others who may share a similar pre-existing culture or idea. Users on VRChat may also use and develop lingo or [[Special:MyLanguage/Community:Terminology|terminology]], based on ideas associated with VRChat.

